headline: Prasad overruled FDA scientists on Moderna application, STAT says
summary: Vinay Prasad, director of the FDA’s Center for Biologics Evaluation and Research, overruled the agency’s reviewers in refusing to accept Moderna’s (MRNA) application for a new influenza vaccine, Lizzy Lawrence of STAT reports, citing three officials familiar with the matter. A team of career scientists was ready to review Moderna’s application, sources told the website.
